Package: optiranger
Title: Optimisation of random forest for classification on microbial community data
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Marine C.",
           family = "Cambon",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "cambonmarine@gmail.com",
           comment = c(ORCID = "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5234-4196"))
Description: `optiranger` contains wrapping functions for random forest classification from the `ranger` package. It allows to train algorithms using several parameter values, and aggregating the microbial community table to different taxonomic levels, to identify the best set of condition to make the classification.
URL: https://github.com/marccamb/optiranger
